Cache cleared without creating default instance

It is possible to pass custom implementation of the cache to the constructor.
However, when the cache is cleared, it is always instantiated with default implementation.

Cache cleared without creating default instance

It is possible to pass custom implementation of the cache to the constructor.
However, when the cache is cleared, it is always instantiated with default implementation.

commit.message: Fixing version conflict in pytest-cov
Fixing lint errors
Fixed DataLoader failing for partial load functions

Fix `print` related typos in the README files

Since this package is Python 3.5+ only, the examples inside the README
files should reflect that; before this change, they where using the
statement form of `print` (which is Python 2.x only) instead of the
function form.
